        p.
          I hate to admit this, but it‚Äôs true.
        p
          | One of the best things you can do for your career is to move to a big city ‚Äî one of the major media centers ‚Äî the places that broadcast to the entire world.
          strong.
            Nothing less than New York, Los Angeles, London, Mumbai, Hong Kong, or maybe San Francisco.
          | (Nashville, Paris, Seoul, or Tokyo only count if you‚Äôre limiting yourself to those markets.)
        p.
          It‚Äôs the place where everything happens. Where the biggest media companies in the world are based. Where the money is flowing. Where the most successful agents, producers, and executives live and work. Where the most ambitious people go.
        p.
          It has a serious energy, because the stakes are high. It‚Äôs not casual. It‚Äôs not a place for a comfortable work/life balance. It‚Äôs fueled by ambition. People go go go.
        p.
          I‚Äôve lived in a bunch of places now, but when I look back at my career, it‚Äôs obvious that the biggest breakthroughs happened because I was living in the heart of the music industry in New York and Los Angeles.
        p
          strong.
            It shows that you‚Äôre in the game.
          | It shows you‚Äôre serious. It gives you healthy competition, knowing that today‚Äôs biggest stars and legends are there with you, too. It challenges you to push your skills to the best of the best, instead of just the best in your home town.
        p.
          Once you‚Äôre famous, and the media is carrying your reputation, you can move away if you want. But even then you‚Äôll be a little out of the game. You can decide if that‚Äôs OK with you.
        p.
          I lived in New York City for nine years, and Los Angeles for seven years. I met so many wonderful kindreds ‚Äî other ambitious people like me that had moved there from around the world to get successful.
        p.
          So why do I hate to admit this?
        p.
          Because I love how the internet has made it possible for anyone to get successful, anywhere. I love the idea of living in the middle of nowhere, surrounded by nature, yet being connected to the world.
        p
          | But still, when I look at the facts, it‚Äôs impossible to deny.

          strong.

            Living in the big city, and being where everything is happening, will help your career the most.

          | Being anywhere else won‚Äôt hurt you, but it won‚Äôt help.

